[SN]TITLE[SN]
Paul Croft death: Second murder charge after cold case probe

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A cold case investigation into the death of a teenager who was beaten with a baseball bat has led to a second man being charged with his murder.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Paul Croft, 19, died in hospital in March 2005, a week after being attacked in an alleyway in Pendlebury, Salford.
Greater Manchester Police's Cold Case Unit reopened an investigation into his death in 2015.
Paul O'Neill, 35, of Broomhall Road in Pendlebury, was remanded into custody by Manchester magistrates.
A 28-year-old man from Swinton was charged with Mr Croft's murder in November.
